    "7233930": {
      "title": "Positive selection and compensatory adaptation interact to stabilize non-transmissible plasmids",
      "abstract": "Plasmids are important for bacterial evolution but the evolutionary mechanisms behind their maintenance are unclear. Here the authors show that the interplay between compensatory adaptation and positive selection for plasmid-encoded antibiotic resistance determines plasmid persistence in P. aeruginosa."
